dark energy at z $>$ 0.57, and when combined imply
$\Omega\Lambda$ = 0.74 $\pm$ 0.016, independent of the
Universe's evolution at z $<$ 0.57. All of these constraints assume
scale-independent linear growth, and assume general relativity to
compute both O(10 per cent) non-linear model corrections and our errors.
